<Author>TravellerinBxl
<Content>A distaster Together with 2 other friends we booked a three-bed room for 5 nights. We were slightly chocked already when we entered the room - it had no windows! It was a humid warm burrow with a false window to some kind of an internal well. But ok, we came to visit Barcelona, not to sit in the hotel room, so we did not spend too much time thinking about that.During the night we couldn't sleep, it was too warm (not working air-co) and too loud (you can here people talking in the corridor, slamming doors, etc), but the worst we were scratching most of the time. I thought (oh, how naive one can be) it's nervous itching, some kind of psychological reaction to the first night in not known place. Unfortunately, in the morning we discovered bugs on our sheets! We identified them as bed-bugs (brrrr), later we've learnt there were also fleas. We packed our staff immediately to change the hotel.But at the reception desk another nasty surprise - we booked the hotel via barcelona30 website and pre-paied by a credit card a certain percentage of the total price which gave almost 90 Euros. When you book the hotel, it is suggested you pre-pay a part of the accomodation price. U-huh, as we've learnt aaalllll 90 Euros was the fee for the booking service! and we still needed to pay extra 80 Euros for the spent night there. I'm still to write a formal complaint to the barcelona30 company, and I will not hesitate to take legal steps, as it's simple cheating. All together an awful adventure.And as for the bugs, we were so badly bitten, that we needed a dermatological assistance - we are still taking anti-alergic pills and apply a special ointment. I wish I have taken photos of red spots on my feet and swallowed wrists so I could send them to the hotel. Higly not-recommended place to stay. 
