<Content>Dirty, old and horrible hostal with mean and unfriendly people at the reception II booked the room at Hostal Paris through the website [--] for one week (7 nights) where they charge you 87鈧?straight away and tell you that each night comes out to 59鈧?. The price seemed reasonable and after reading reviews about the hostal it seemed quite nice. But it was absolutely awful. It is extremely old and very ugly. The rooms are dirty, the bed sheets very used and the towels have holes. The soap in the bathroom belonged to another hotel. The bed had bugs and and me and my friend were bitten while trying to sleep during the 1st and only night (as we booked another hotel just 20鈧?more and on the Ramblas with breakfast and a fantastic room with a wonderful view and soundproof windows). The noise you can hear in the Hostal Paris is the same as if you were outside, or the people talking, screaming, laughing and cars, ambulances were inside your room making a huge noise until the morning. The 2 people at the reception of the hostal do not know how to smile (nor even understand any other language beside Spanish) The night receptionist told us when we said we were leaving the next day that we did not have to pay anything more as we had already paid 87鈧? The next morning when we checked out, the lady at the reception screamed at us saying that we had to pay an extra 53,50鈧?(after already having paid 87鈧? for one night. Said that the 87鈧?was barcelona30 commission, but that鈥檚 not what barcelona30 said before, never had they said that the room was 53鈧?0 per night (they said 59鈧? it was a horrible 1st night in Barcelona (a fantastic city that we were visiting for the 1st time). It is a dreadful hostal, horrible rooms, very unfriendly and badly educated people who work there. I do not recommend this hostel to anyone. Absolutely the worst thing with mean uneducated screaming people working there, that I鈥檝e ever encountered in my life. 
