<Author>aessedai
<Content>not bad for location and price we are staying here at the moment (21st of May 2006) and so far so good. we drove down this morning from the sth of france and after a major stuff up by La Terrassa hotel we walked into Hostal Paris (first place we found off Las Ramblas) and asked if they had a triple availble. Yes. How much? 75 euros. Done! we inspected the room and it is clean, three single beds, a clean and large bathroom with shower/bath, a tv and an airconditioner. it was up the first flight of stairs and towards the back...the windows open into a central air well (not pretty to look out on but quiet and decent air flow). they don麓t serve breakfast but there is a great cafe around the corner that does a full english breakfast for 6.50 euros incl coffee and juice or plenty of tapas places or pastry shops nearby. you are two seconds from las ramblas and in a perfect location for price. since we drove down we had to park the car somewhere and parked under the cathedral. 30 euros for 24 hrs. certainly not cheap but close by and only paying 25 euros each for accomodation meant 30 was fine (even when converted into aussie dollars!!). as mentioned above by others the staff (husband and wife i think) aren麓t exactly a ball of fun but i suspect that is because of the language more than anything else. they are always polite and try and help.so, in all, for the price a pretty good deal. certainly not luxury but clean and awesome location. 
