<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Don't look down! Very basic -- rather creaky and rickety beds with tasteless 1970's sheets, but the shower had a plentiful supply of hot water. Got our own bathroom, and the toilet and shower were well-cleaned and worked as they should. There were a few problems with air conditioning -- we stayed in September and it was quite humid at night, and we definitely felt it even with the air conditioning switched on. No lift, and at least five flights of steep stairs, so not idea for people with heart problems/lack of upper body strength! The location was quite good -- very close to Las Ramblas and Passeig de Gracia metro station, and for 20 Euros a night we could have done a great deal worse. Gorgeous ice cream shop selling a myriad of flavors (including 'blue ice' which tasted like raspberry jam for some reason!) is few moments north from the amusement arcade. The Erotica Museum is also nearby, as is the Chamption Supermarket (great place to pick up a litre bottle of water for 30 cents!)The staff didn't seem particularly friendly or unfriendly due to the language barrier. We didn't speak Catalonian and they didn't speak English, but they were patient in writing everything down for us and understanding out really bad Spanish/Catalan hybrid. The security wasn't the best -- simple key lock for the doors and wire lock for the windows, so make sure you take passports, etc. with you when you leave the hotel for the day just for peace of mind.Basically, it's clean, fairly comfortable and basic, and if you're staying on a budget and want a room to yourself for washing and crashing, I'd recommend it. 
